theorem closure_diff_frontier_eq_interior {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] (A : Set X) :
    closure A \ frontier A = interior A := by
  -- We prove the two inclusions separately via set extensionality.
  ext x
  constructor
  · intro hx
    rcases hx with ⟨hx_cl, hx_not_front⟩
    by_cases hx_int : x ∈ interior A
    · exact hx_int
    · -- If `x ∉ interior A` but `x ∈ closure A`, then `x ∈ frontier A`,
      -- contradicting `hx_not_front`.
      have h_front_eq :
          (frontier A : Set X) = closure A \ interior A :=
        frontier_eq_closure_diff_interior (X := X) (A := A)
      have hx_front : x ∈ frontier A := by
        have : x ∈ (closure A \ interior A) := And.intro hx_cl hx_int
        simpa [h_front_eq] using this
      exact (hx_not_front hx_front).elim
  · intro hx_int
    have hx_cl : x ∈ closure A := subset_closure (interior_subset hx_int)
    have hx_not_front : x ∉ frontier A := by
      intro hx_front
      -- A point in the frontier is outside `interior A`, contradiction.
      exact hx_front.2 hx_int
    exact And.intro hx_cl hx_not_front
